  <條文>
    <條號>Article 48</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[When it [the competent authority] deems necessary in Article 28 of this Act means one of the circumstances listed in the subparagraphs in Article 19 that is still unable to be resolved after being handled pursuant to other related regulations and orders.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 49</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The written report for conducting a survey and analysis of environmental impact and submitting response strategies pursuant to Article 28 of this Act shall record the following items.
ⅠThe name and business address or office address of the developer
ⅡThe name, permanent residence address, temporary residence address and identification number of the statutory responsible person
ⅢThe name and site of the development activity
ⅣThe purpose and content of the development activity
ⅤEnvironmental protection strategies adopted for the development activity and their results.
ⅥCurrent environmental conditions.
ⅦKnown and forecast environmental impacts of the development activity.
ⅧStrategies for the mitigation and prevention of adverse environmental impacts
ⅨAlternate plan
ⅩBudget required for the implementation of response strategies
XIReference bibliography
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 50</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The relevant competent authority in Article 29 of this Act means the agency that performs the original review of an environmental impact statement or environmental impact assessment reports prior to this Act taking effect.
The agency in the foregoing paragraph shall perform supervision work pursuant to article 18 of this Act; the competent authority may implement said supervision work in conjunction with the agency in the foregoing paragraph.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 51</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Article 36 through Article 38 shall apply, where appropriate, to those environmental impact statements or environmental impact assessment reportss that are already completed prior to this Act taking effect and for which review conclusions have been prepared following review and to those developers that apply to modify the contents of an original application.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 51-1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[When the central industry competent authority, municipality or county (city) government proposes recommendations for revision based on the identification standard, detailed items or laws relevant to environmental impact assessment work, it shall invite related agencies and diversified private groups to have a public discussion then integrate consensus to a proposal in an official letter to request the central competent authority to have a public hearing which the treatment shall be made in accordance with legal procedure by the central competent authority.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 52</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The central competent authority shall determine the format for all disciplinary citations, letters of appointment and other documents and forms designated in this Act and these Rules
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 53</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These Rules shall take effect from the date of promulgation.
Except for Articles 5.1, 11.1 and 12 that were announced on 3 July 2015 and implemented six months after announcement, those revised rules shall be implemented at the time of announcement.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
